title: High Crop Production Index
description: In 2022, Senegal achieved a Crop Production Index of 189.93, indicating a significant increase in agricultural productivity compared to the 2014-2016 baseline.

title: Strong Food Production Growth
description: Senegal's Food Production Index reached 177.49 in 2022, showcasing robust growth in food production since the 2014-2016 period.

title: Gender Parity in Primary Education
description: In 2021, Senegal's Gender Parity Index for primary school enrollment was 1.164, reflecting a higher enrollment rate for girls compared to boys.

title: Gender Parity in Primary and Secondary Education
description: The Gender Parity Index for primary and secondary education in Senegal was 1.176 in 2021, indicating a favorable balance towards female enrollment.

title: High Female Enrollment in Primary Education
description: In 2018, 52.52% of primary education pupils in Senegal were female, highlighting a positive trend towards gender equality in education.

title: Low Women's Participation in Decision-Making
description: Only 10.2% of women aged 15-49 in Senegal participated in key decision-making areas in 2019, indicating a need for improved gender equality.

title: Negative Net Aid from Slovenia
description: In 2020, Senegal experienced a net negative bilateral aid flow of $140,000 from Slovenia, reflecting a financial outflow rather than support.
